# Tailwind Usage Rules (Stronger Enforcement)

## Allowed

- Layout utilities (`flex`, `grid`, etc.)
- Spacing utilities (`p-4`, `mt-2`, `gap-3`, etc.)
- Border/radius/shadow utilities

## Not Allowed

- Arbitrary values (e.g. `p-[13px]`)
- Raw Tailwind palette color utilities (e.g. `text-green-500`, `bg-gray-100`)
- Hardcoded color values:
  - no `#hex`, `rgb()`, `rgba()`, `hsl()` in inline styles
  - no hardcoded colors in CSS/SCSS/style props

## Semantic Colors Only

- Colors must always come from semantic tokens only.
- Do NOT fallback to palette colors if a semantic token is missing.
- If a required semantic token is missing, request it instead of inventing a fallback.
- Use token-based color classes derived from your semantic token keys (e.g. `text-primary`, `bg-background`).

## Dark Mode

- Prefer semantic utilities so colors track `dark-mode.css` under a `.dark` ancestor. Avoid raw palette `dark:*` utilities (e.g. `dark:bg-gray-800`); if design differs, add a semantic token with light + dark values instead.

